The above example compiles with ECJ but shows error with b120.

(JSR 335, 15.28 : If a method reference has the form super :: NonWildTypeArgumentsopt Identifier, let T be the type declaration immediately enclosing the method reference. It is a compile-time error if T is the class Object or T is an interface.)</thetext>
